  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Prevention of violence in Central America and youth empowerment</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Youth prevention and protection against violence should consider the multifaceted and complex nature of its causes and consequences among young people. Actions need to take into account lessons learned in terms of accurate prevention measures. Treatment practices show that it is better to accentuate prevention and rehabilitation rather than mere repression; that the social causes which fuel violence need to be addressed, prioritizing a human rights approach in dealing with violent youth; that it is better to engage the entire environment of young people in these policies; and that rehabilitation should be promoted by considering the motivations of young people themselves.</narrative>
  </description>
